# B. UI Implementation and User Interaction

The system interface is implemented as a web-based UI interacting with the backend forensic analysis server.

## 1. Login Interface

Users must authenticate before accessing the system.

### Components
- Username field
- Password field
- Role selection
- Login button

### Example UI Code
<form>
<label>Username:</label>
<input type="text" name="username">

<label>Password:</label>
<input type="password" name="password">

<label>Role:</label>
<select>
<option>Administrator</option>
<option>Investigator</option>
<option>Analyst</option>
</select>

<button>Login</button>
</form>

## 2. Dashboard Interface (Menu-Based)

After login, users see a dashboard with menu options.

### Example Menu

Digital Forensics Dashboard

- Create Case
- Upload Evidence
- View Evidence
- Run Analysis
- Chain of Custody
- Generate Report
- Logout

Users select operations by clicking the menu buttons.

## 3. Evidence Upload Interface (Direct Manipulation)

The evidence upload page allows users to drag and drop files.

### Example

Upload Evidence → [ Drag & Drop Files Here ]  
or  
[ Browse Files ]

### User Interaction

Investigator drags a forensic image file → System uploads the file to the server → Evidence ID is generated.

## 4. Analysis Interaction

Users select evidence and run analysis.

### Example Interaction

Select Evidence: EV204  
Analysis Type: Metadata Extraction  

[Run Analysis]

### System Output

Analysis Completed  
Files Found: 120  
Deleted Files Recovered: 32  

## 5. Chain of Custody Viewer

The system displays evidence handling history.

### Example

Case ID: CASE102

| Timestamp | Action | User |
|----------|--------|------|
| 10:10 AM | Case Created | Investigator |
| 10:12 AM | Evidence Uploaded | Investigator |
| 10:20 AM | Analysis Run | Analyst |

## Conclusion

The Digital Forensics Investigation System uses a hybrid user interface combining Menu-Based and Direct Manipulation approaches.

The menu-based interface provides structured navigation across system modules, while the direct manipulation interface allows intuitive interaction with evidence files and analysis tools.

This combination improves usability, efficiency, and overall user experience.
